The paper discusses the design and functionality of mobile networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the roles of computing and caching in mobile systems, which could fall under the categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), systems and control (cs.SY), and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses practical examples of mobile systems, including media content delivery, which could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
